#import "/_lib/0.1.1.typ": *
#show: template

#taxon[Definition]
#title[Finite morphism]

A morphism of schemes $pi : X -> Y$ is finite if it is #local("00BT")[affine] and for every affine open $"Spec"(B) subset Y$, the open subscheme $pi^(-1) "Spec" (B)) subset X$ is the afine scheme $"Spec"(A)$ of a finite $B$-algebra $A$.
